article.description: Dewanna Bonner led Auburn (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today, No. 14 AP) with 26 points and 11 rebounds in a 95-74 victory over North Carolina A&T on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Auburn capitalizes on North Carolina A&T miscues
article.linkText: Auburn takes advantage of North Carolina A&T
article.story:
AUBURN, Ala. -- Dewanna Bonner led Auburn (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today, No. 14 AP) with 26 points and 11 rebounds in a 95-74 victory over North Carolina A&T on Wednesday night.

Three Tigers scored in double digits alongside Bonner, including Sherell Hobbs and Travesha Jackson with 16 points and Whitney Boddie with 10.

Auburn (8-0) led 45-42 at halftime, before outscoring the Aggies (3-3) 50-32 in the second half.

Brittany Taylor-James led the Aggies with 18 points and nine rebounds. Jaleesa Sams scored 15, while Amber Bland and Lamona Smalley added 12 and 11, respectively.

The Tigers scored 28 points off 17 Aggie turnovers. Auburn stole the ball eight times, as Jordan Greenleaf, Morgan Jennings, Alli Smalley and Bonner had two steals each.

Auburn had 17 offensive rebounds, which helped the Tigers tally 16 second-chance points.
